<br>
My dissatisfaction with the cleric class is purely my own.  Though I've seen similar complaints from other clerics, I can't speak for them.  This rant is -my- rant and it's coming from a very burned out player.<br>
<br>
Clerics are required for raids.  Clerics are the howitzer of healing classes, and without them a guild just won't progress very far.  'Need more clerics' is almost a mantra in Noble Blade, and always has been.  Clerics are valued and pampered.<br>
<br>
You would think that all of this attention would make clerics more desirable a class, but the truth is that all of the power of the cleric is focused into one thing:  The boss fight.  On any given raid with 8 to 10 clerics, you may need 2 clerics to manage all of the content up to whatever your next named mob is.  This was most apparent in Vex Thal, but I've also found it to be true as we struggle through the elemental content.<br>
<br>
A cleric shows up and the raid spends hours clearing, while the clerics huddle in a protected group surrounded by the rest of the raid.  There's no need to learn the zone as a cleric.  There's not really any need to even see the mobs that you're fighting.  Most of your clerics don't even need to be AT the raid until the boss is pulled.  On an 8 hour raid, I may only spend an hour of that time actually doing anything, unless I'm the main tank healer during the trash clearing.<br>
<br>
Outside of that boss mob healing role, clerics are pitifully underpowered.  A good cleric can use his 1100 point nukes to help clear the yard trash, but that contribution is pretty sad when you examine the cast/recast of those spells compared to every other DPS class in the game.  You won't really notice it if your idle clerics don't nuke.<br>
<br>
I got sick of it some time ago and levelled my necromancer to 65.  That's when I really discovered just how miserable the cleric is.  With the necro, I have instant access to XP at any time when we aren't raiding.  Though a necro isn't all that great in groups, Sony has managed to upgrade them to the point where they serve equally as well as most classes in that role.  On raids, necromancers have become superb damage dealers who can offer a vital contribution, especially against those mobs that the melees can't touch for fear of AE rampage or suchlike.<br>
<br>
The necromancer interacts with the environment.  As a cleric, I watch red bars.  My attention is focused on others and not on the environment.  With the necromancer I'm actively doing something useful most of the time, and not just twiddling my thumbs or making work for myself with some worthless magic-based nuke that might hit for 200 points of damage if it's not completely resisted.<br>
<br>
Perhaps if I'd never played a necromancer, I'd still be happy with my cleric, but logging in Borick, for all of the gear I've carefully built up over the years, leaves me feeling like a powerless cripple compared to my necromancer in all of his Kael quest armor.<br>
<br>
I'm sick of being required and obligated to attend with a class that nobody ever has enough of.  I'm sick of never having enough of that class to do the job right, and I'm just sick of grouping, healing and generally playing a support role.   I think that if Sony just gave the healing power of clerics to shamans and druids, the game might survive a little bit longer.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jurrasicepoch>Jurrasic Epoch</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FK Rep</span><br>  Posts: 1209<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(7/27/03 10:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1308.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://thegeekhost.com/gravedirt/friend.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Clerics?</span><hr size=1> Having dropped a cleric main to roll Jurrasic, I know exactly how he feels as well, though it was quite a bit longer ago and well before the high end of EQ as we know it was formed. <br>
