You can make what you want out of any class, sure, but the telling differences that single out clerics and make it not just a matter of pushing a button are these:<br>
<br>
Attentiveness.  100% attentiveness is required by a cleric, yet that attention is only actually needed at a very small percentage of the raid.  Clerics are very 'hurry up and wait', hovering over a heal key in the off chance that someone grabs aggro.<br>
<br>
Obligation.  Clerics are obligated more than any other class in the game to help their guild and friends at all times.  This is even worse if your team doesn't require attendance at raids.  Those who show up tend to be burdened with far more responsibility.<br>
<br>
Support.  Some people like this.  I did it for a long time and love the feeling of power that came with people relying on me.  But that has grown stale.  I want to directly effect and control the environment.  I want to do things TO the mobs, not keep someone else alive so that they can do it.  It's a narrow distinction, and the weakest of my arguments, and the one most based upon personal feeling.<br>
<br>
You can make work for yourself, but in any role other than healing, a cleric comes in dead last in DPS and general utility.  Dead last.  <br>
<br>
Couple that with the fact that I hate grouping for my XP, and the cleric has just turned out to be a really bad choice.  I often wish that Sony would allow us to transfer our no-drop gear to other guildmates when we retire. :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elanacurvacious>ElanaCurvacious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(7/29/03 9:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1308.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.icode4food.com/images/bananaMan.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> I like my cleric. It sure as heck keeps me on my toes. I'm actually useful compared to my mage but my bard was definetly the most fun/challenging to play. And if you think clerics are boring try being on a raid with 50+ ppl and being one of only 5 or so clerics that decided to log on and be one of the few non afk ones and try to keep everyone alive while pulling. Daraan found out the hard way while playing me when I had to go afk to make dinner...&quot;Wow. I actually have to do stuff.&quot;<br>
