I played a cleric to 54 before my account was hacked and Ssarvhok became my main. In exp groups my cleric usually:<br>
<br>
1) Pulled; 3 roots + distance agro = win <br>
2) Did crowd control; fast root &gt; crappy ench always<br>
3) Did fear-kite groups; rog+rng+clr = dps+snare+fear<br>
4) Stopped casters from casting; stuns = own<br>
5) Tanked; (3 rogues + cleric in Kunark-era Sol B, rar!) <br>
6) Nuked; Could solo Undead and Drolvarg alike (not fast)<br>
7) Occasionally healed people<br>
<br>
Nowadays I still see clerics doing all of those except #3; plenty of off-tank or tank-happy clerics still out there. Plenty of clerics who actually know how to crowd control, interrupt casters, know when to nuke, enjoy pulling, etc.<br>
