<br>
Rotations are kinda boring, but in PoP most rotations are so fast that you don't get bored, you end up almost chain casting.  Unlike Seru, where you can have a 6 cleric 6 sec rotation for an hour, and fall asleep cuz of the long delay.<br>
<br>
As for the lack of ability to solo, I disagree with that.  You just have to be more patient and be willing to take a lower return on xp than other classes (like wizard) would get.  I don't know of many mages that solo at high end without using charm, due to lack of a valuable spell:  root.  And yet, I don't hear constant whining from them about it.<br>
<br>
Don't forget Clerics are a plate class.  This means that you can tank, when needed.  Quite often on my cleric I will purposefully heal early in order to get agro so that the chanter will have time to mez instead of having to tank.  I do the same thing on charm breaks.<br>
<br>
Can healing get boring?  Sure it can, but so can anything else.  Wizards to be would end up being just as boring, cuz their most frequently used ability is nuking, and that's mostly (but not all) that they do.<br>
<br>
I feel privledged to play one of the backbone classes of the game, and I see rewards for it.  Clerics (especially in the old day) tend to get the better loot first (poor druids..../cry).  Clerics get treated better, both on and off raids.  I get invited to kite groups alot for xp, even though I'm low DPS, because people like me and recognize the value of a well aa'd cleric.  (2.3 cast heal that can crit for over 7k owns).<br>
<br>
It sounds to me, though, that you're just really burned out on playing your cleric.  So I think you're doing the right thing by playing your necro.  The whole point of a game / hobby / recreational activity like EQ is to have fun.  So do what lets you have fun.  In a few months, when you get burned on your necro, and start thinking about complaining how you're not doing anything but dps and feeding mana, you'll be able to swap back to your cleric and have fun with him.<br>
<br>
I know because I've let cleric friends play my enchanter before, and usually within a month or so I would get a thank you, cuz I had shown them a different side of EQ and they were enjoying their clerics more again because of it.<br>
<br>
I wish you the best of luck, and hope you are able to find and stay happy in EQ.  =-)<br>
<br>
Heffling / Seranis<br>
